 * Editor's note: If you have trouble viewing the livestream, please click here.JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba and the CEO of the Independent Regulatory Board for Auditors, Bernard Agulhas, will brief the media on regulation of audit firms.Gigaba said a study revealed that black-owned auditing firms are struggling to make inroads.He also stressed the lack of transformation.Gigaba said the biggest proportion of investments of both black and white South Africans is held through mandated investments.Tweets about Gigaba AND(FROM:@karynmaughan since:2017-06-02 until:2017-06-03) * Editor's note:This livestream is now over. Watch the recording above.JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba and the CEO of the Independent Regulatory Board for Auditors, Bernard Agulhas, will brief the media on regulation of audit firms.Gigaba said a study revealed that black-owned auditing firms are struggling to make inroads.He also stressed the lack of transformation.Gigaba said the biggest proportion of investments of both black and white South Africans is held through mandated investments.Tweets about Gigaba AND(FROM:@karynmaughan since:2017-06-02 until:2017-06-03) eNCA